]]''\n|-\n| [[Martha Wells]] || ''[[All Systems Red]]''\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tor.com/2019/01/14/announcing-the-nominees-for-the-2019-philip-k-dick-award/|title=Announcing the Nominees for the 2019 Philip K. Dick Award|website=[[Tor.com]]|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=29 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''[[Audrey Schulman]] '''|| '''''[[Theory of Bastards]]'''''\n|-\n| ''[[Claire North]]'' || ''[[84K]]''\n|-\n| [[Ian McDonald (British author)|Ian McDonald]] || ''[[Time Was (novel)|Time Was]]''\n|-\n| [[Jeff Noon]] || ''[[The Body Library]]''\n|-\n| [[Abbey Mei Otis]] || ''[[Alien Virus Love Disaster: Stories]]''\n|-\n| [[Vandana Singh]] || ''[[Ambiguity Machines and Other Stories]]''\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.philipkdickaward.org/2020/01/2020-philip-k-dick-award-nominees-announced.html/|title=2020 Philip K. Dick Award Nominees Announced|website=[[philipkdickaward.org]]|date=13 January 2020|accessdate=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''[[Sarah Pinsker]]''' || '''''[[Sooner or Later Everything Falls Into the Sea: Stories]]'''''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.philipkdickaward.org/2020/04/2020-philip-k-dick-award-winner-announced.html/|title=2020 Philip K. Dick Award Winner Announced|website=[[philipkdickaward.org]]|date=10 April 2020|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Sarah Tolmie]]'' || ''[[The Little Animals]]''\n|-\n| [[Ada Hoffmann]] || ''[[The Outside (novel)|The Outside]]''\n|-\n| [[Megan E. O'Keefe]] || ''[[Velocity Weapon]]''\n|-\n| [[Susan Palwick]] || ''[[All Worlds Are Real: Short Fictions]]''\n|-\n| [[Tade Thompson ]] || ''[[The Rosewater Redemption]]''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.philipkdickaward.org}}\n* [http://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_pkd.asp List of all winning and nominated novels]\n\n{{science fiction}}\n{{Philip K. Dick}}\n\n[[Category:Science fiction awards]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1983]]\n[[Category:American literary awards]]\n[[Category:American speculative fiction awards|D]]\n[[Category:Philip K. Dick]]\n[[Category:Philip K. Dick Award-winning works| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = Philip K. Dick Award\n| image          = \n| imagesize      = 150px\n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| current_awards = \n| description    = The best [[science fiction]] paperback novel published in the United States in the previous calendar year\n| presenter      = [[Philadelphia Science Fiction Society]], [[Philip K. Dick Trust]], [[Northwest Science Fiction Society]]\n| country        = United States\n| location       = \n| year           = 1983\n| website        = [http://www.philipkdickaward.org/ philipkdickaward.org]\n}}\nThe '''Philip K. Dick Award''' is an American [[List of science fiction awards|science fiction award]] given annually at [[Norwescon]] and sponsored by the [[Philadelphia Science Fiction Society]] and (since 2005) the Philip K. Dick Trust.  Named after [[science fiction]] and fantasy writer [[Philip K. Dick]], it has been awarded since 1983, the year after his death.  It is awarded to the best original paperback published each year in the US.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Pkd.html|title=Locus index to SF Awards|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090412205849/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/Pkd.html|archivedate=2009-04-12|df=}}</ref>\n\nThe award was founded by [[Thomas Disch]] with assistance from [[David G. Hartwell]], [[Paul S. Williams]], and [[Charles N. Brown]]. As of 2016, it is administered by [[Pat LoBrutto]], John Silbersack, and [[Gordon Van Gelder]].  Past administrators include [[Algis Budrys]], David G. Hartwell, and David Alexander Smith.\n\n== Winners and nominees ==\nWinners are listed in '''bold'''.<br>\nAuthors of special citation entries are listed in ''italics''. The year in the table below indicates the year the book 