{"title_page": "List of twin towns and sister cities in the Republic of Ireland", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}}\nThis is a '''list of places in Ireland''' having standing links to local communities in other countries. In most cases, the association, especially when formalised by [[Local government in the Republic of Ireland|local government]], is known as \"[[Sister cities|town twinning]]\" (though other terms, such as \"partner towns\" or \"sister cities\" are sometimes used instead), and while most of the places included are towns, the list also comprises villages, cities, districts, counties, etc. with similar links.\n\n[[File:Sign showing Greystones, Ireland, as a twin city to Holyhead, Wales.jpg|thumb|Sign posted at the entrance of Greystones, Co. Wicklow, Ireland, stating that the city is twinned with Holyhead, in Wales.]]\n\nThe list is arranged by [[Provinces of Ireland|province]]; and then by the [[Counties of Ireland|county]]. It forms part of the larger [[list of twin towns and sister cities]].\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==[[Connacht]]==\n\n===County Galway===\n*[[Galway]] -\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge]], [[Massachusetts]], [[United States]]<ref>{{cite web |title=GalwayCity - Town Twinning |url=https://www.galwaycity.ie/town-twinning-information |website=Galway City Council |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Illinois}} [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], United States<ref>{{cite web |title=Galway, Ireland: Sister City since 1997 |publisher=Chicago Sister Cities International |date=2013 |url=http://chicagosistercities.com/sister-cities/galway/ |accessdate=19 May 2017 }}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|California}} [[Menlo Park, California]], United States<ref>{{cite web |title=Sister City Program |url=https://www.menlopark.org/1045/Sister-City-program |website=City of Menlo Park |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Missouri}} [[Saint Louis, Missouri]], United States <ref>{{cite web |title=Galway, Ireland: Sister City |url=http://www.sistercities.org/interactive-map/St.%20Louis,%20Missouri |accessdate=18 December 2017 }}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Washington}} [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], United States<ref>{{cite web |title=Galway, Ireland |work=Office of Intergovernmental Relations |publisher=City of Seattle |date=2016 |url=http://www.seattle.gov/oir/sister-cities/seattles-21-sister-cities/galway |accessdate=19 May 2017 }}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Wisconsin}} [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]], United States<ref>{{cite web |title=Milwaukee's Sister Cities |url=https://city.milwaukee.gov/commoncouncil/sistercities#.XICR5Ij7SM8 |website=Official Website of the City of Milwaukee |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{flagicon|England}} [[Bradford]], [[United Kingdom]] <ref>{{cite news |title=Small town, would like to meet... |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/small-town-would-like-to-meet-1.739544|accessdate=7 March 2019 |agency=The Irish Times |publisher=The Irish Times |date=7 April 2009}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Brittany}} [[Lorient]], [[Brittany]], [[France]] <ref>{{cite news |title=Galway host to twinned cities |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/galway-host-to-twinned-cities-1.53175 |accessdate=7 March 2019 |agency=The Irish Times |publisher=The Irish Times |date=18 March 1997}}</ref>\n\n*[[Athenry]] -\n:{{flagicon|FRA}}{{flagicon|Brittany}} [[Quimperl\u00e9]], Brittany, France<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.letelegramme.fr/ar/viewarticle1024.php?aaaammjj=20070212&article=20070212-323481&type=ar |title=Jumelage Quimperl\u00e9-Athenry: P\u00e2ques en Irlande |date=12 February 2007 |website=[[Le T\u00e9l\u00e9gramme]] |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612233723/http://www.letelegramme.fr/ar/viewarticle1024.php?aaaammjj=20070212&article=20070212-323481&type=ar |archive-date=12 June 2017 |url-status=live |access-date=12 June 2017}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|CAN}}{{flagicon|Newfoundland and Labrador}} [[Renews-Cappahayden]], [[Newfoundland and Labrador]], [[Canada]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.advertiser.ie/galway/article/63523/athenry-twinned-with-newfoundland-town |title=Athenry twinned with Newfoundland town |date=5 September 2013 |work=[[Galway Advertiser]] |access-date=12 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612233007/http://www.advertiser.ie/galway/article/63523/athenry-twinned-with-newfoundland-town |archive-date=12 June 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*[[Ballymoe]] -\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Nebraska}} [[Boys Town, Nebraska|Boys Town]], [[Nebraska]], United States<ref name=\"US embassy list\">{{cite web |title=Sister Cities |url=https://ie.usembassy.gov/our-relationship/policy-history/sister-cities/ |website=U.S. Embassy in Ireland |accessdate=7 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n*[[Oranmore]] - \n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Brittany}} [[Clohars-Fouesnant]], Brittany, France <ref>{{cite news |title=Oranmore twins with Breton village |url=https://www.advertiser.ie/index.php/galway/article/51366/oranmore-twins-with-breton-village |accessdate=7 March 2019 |agency=The Galway Advertiser |publisher=The Galway Advertiser |date=19 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n*[[Tuam]] - \n:{{flagicon|Germany}} [[Straubing, Germany|Straubing]], [[Lower Bavaria]], Germany <ref>{{cite web |title=Tuam - Straubing Twinning |url=http://www.tuam-straubing.ie/ |website=Tuam - Straubing Twinning |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===County Leitrim===\n\n===County Mayo===\n\n*[[Ballina, County Mayo|Ballina]] - {{Flagicon|United States}}{{Flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Pittsfield, Massachusetts|Pittsfield]], [[Massachusetts]], United States<ref name=\"US embassy list\"/>\n\n===County Sligo===\n\n====Sligo Town (borough)====\n\n*[[Sligo]] - {{Flagicon|United States}}{{Flagicon|Florida}} [[Tallahassee, Florida|Tallahassee]], [[Florida]], United States<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tallahasseeirish.org/?page_id=116|title=The Friends of Sligo Ireland Sponsor Irish Related Events|website=Tallahassee Irish Society|access-date=2018-11-08}}</ref>\n\n==[[Leinster]]==\n\n===County Carlow===\n\n*[[Carlow]]\n*[[Hacketstown]] -\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|NJ}} [[Hackettstown, New Jersey]], United States<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lehighvalleylive.com/warren-county/express-times/index.ssf/2011/03/hackettstown_nj_declares_frien.html|title=Hackettstown, N.J., declares 'sister city' relationship with Hacketstown, Ireland|work=lehighvalleylive.com|access-date=2017-06-14|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===County Dublin===\n\n====Dublin City====\n*[[Dublin]] \u2013\n:{{flagicon|ESP}}{{flagicon|CAT}} [[Barcelona]], Catalunya, Spain (1998)<ref name=\"Barcelona\">{{cite web|url=http://w3.bcn.es/XMLServeis/XMLHomeLinkPl/0,4022,229724149_257215678_1,00.html |title=Barcelona internacional \u2013 Ciutats agermanades |publisher=\u00a9 2006\u20132009 [http://www.bcn.es/catala/copyright/welcome2.htm Ajuntament de Barcelona] |language=Spanish |accessdate=13 July 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090216085914/http://w3.bcn.es/XMLServeis/XMLHomeLinkPl/0%2C4022%2C229724149_257215678_1%2C00.html |archivedate=16 February 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>[http://www.dublincity.ie/sites/default/files/content/YourCouncil/AbouttheCouncil/CouncilDepartments/Documents/Memorandum_of_Understanding.pdf ADDENDUM OF THE TWINNING AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE CITY OF DUBLIN AND THE CITY OF BARCELONA] (2013). Dublin City Council. Retrieved 9 January 2019</ref>\n:{{flagicon|CHN}} [[Beijing]], People's Republic of China <ref name=\"Dublin City Council\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dublincity.ie/main-menu-services-press-and-news/facts-about-dublin-city |title=Facts about Dublin City |website=Dublin City Council |accessdate=25 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140711014408/http://www.dublincity.ie