cal communities in other countries. In most cases, the association, especially when formalised by [[Local government in the Republic of Ireland|local government]], is known as \"[[Sister cities|town twinning]]\" (though other terms, such as \"partner towns\" or \"sister cities\" are sometimes used instead), and while most of the places included are towns, the list also comprises villages, cities, districts, counties, etc. with similar links.\n\n[[File:Sign showing Greystones, Ireland, as a twin city to Holyhead, Wales.jpg|thumb|Sign posted at the entrance of Greystones, Co. Wicklow, Ireland, stating that the city is twinned with Holyhead, in Wales.]]\n\nThe list is arranged by [[Provinces of Ireland|province]]; and then by the [[Counties of Ireland|county]]. It forms part of the larger [[list of twin towns and sister cities]].\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==[[Connacht]]==\n\n===County Galway===\n*[[Galway]] -\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge]], [[Massachusetts]], [[United States]]<ref>{{cite web |title=GalwayCity - Town Twinning |url=https://www.galwaycity.ie/town-twinning-information |website=Galway City Council |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Illinois}} [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], United States<ref>{{cite web |title=Galway, Ireland: Sister City since 1997 |publisher=Chicago Sister Cities International |date=2013 |url=http://chicagosistercities.com/sister-cities/galway/ |accessdate=19 May 2017 }}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|California}} [[Menlo Park, California]], United States<ref>{{cite web |title=Sister City Program |url=https://www.menlopark.org/1045/Sister-City-program |website=City of Menlo Park |accessdate=7 March 2019}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{{flagicon|Missouri}} [[Saint Louis, Missouri]], United States <ref>{{cite web |title=Galway, Ireland: Sister City |url=http://www.sistercities.org/interactive-map/St.%20Louis,%20Missouri |accessdate=18 December 2017 }}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|USA}}{