ren travelled too 'because of length of trips'|publisher=Wicklow People|url= https://www.independent.ie/regionals/wicklowpeople/news/junkets-spouses-and-children-travelled-too-because-of-length-of-trips-29251064.html|date=2017|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|Germany}}{{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[W\u00fcrzburg]], [[Bavaria]], [[Germany]] (1999)<ref name=\"Wicklow County Council\"/><ref name=\"Wicklow-W\u00fcrzburg\">{{cite web|title=Two-decade friendship between Wicklow and W\u00fcrzburg renewed|publisher=Bray People|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/braypeople/news/two-decade-friendship-between-wicklow-and-wurzburg-renewed-38664180.html|date=2019|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n*[[Arklow]]\n:{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{flagicon|Wales}} [[Aberystwyth]], [[Wales]], [[United Kingdom]] (2016)<ref name=\"Arklow-Aberystwyth\">{{cite web|title=Town Twinning|publisher=Aberystwyth Council|date=2020|url=https://www.aberystwyth.gov.uk/en/community/town-twinning/|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Centre-Val de Loire}} [[Ch\u00e2teaudun]], [[Centre-Val de Loire]], [[France]] (1983)<ref name=\"Wicklow County Council\"/><ref name=\"Arklow-Ch\u00e2teaudun\">{{cite web|title=Arklow to celebrate 35 years of twinning with Chateaudun|publisher=Wicklow People|date=2017|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/wicklowpeople/news/arklow-to-celebrate-35-years-of-twinning-with-chateaudun-36886800.html|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n*[[Bray, County Wicklow|Bray]]\n:{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Nouvelle-Aquitaine}} [[B\u00e8gles]], [[Nouvelle-Aquitaine]], [[France]] (1994)<ref name=\"Wicklow County Council\"/><ref name=\"Bray-B\u00e8gles\">{{cite web|title=Twinned with B\u00e8gles|url=https://www.bray.ie/twinned-begles/|publisher=bray.ie|date=2020|accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n:{{flagicon|United States}}{{flagicon|California}} [[Dublin, California|Dublin]], [[California]], [[United States]] (1987)<ref name=\"Wicklow County Council\"